<page>
   <topic>FILE.SIZE Function</topic>
   <syntax>Byte_Size as N = file.size(C filename )</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>filename</name>
         <description>The name of the file.</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
   <description>Returns the size of a file</description>
   <discussion>
The FILE.SIZE() method returns the size of a file.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
? file.size("C:\Databases\AlphaMovies\Customers.Ddd")
= 4149
]]></example>
   
